== Roasted Vegetables ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash
and dry all produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise (quarter any larger ones if
necessary). Dice @Sweet Potato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Toss Brussels sprouts and sweet potato on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@oil{some}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the
next step), @salt{some}, and @pepper{some}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Meatloaves ==

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, stir together @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup} and
@water{2%tbsp}. (TIP: Have milk on hand? Use it in place of water for an even
more flavorful meatloaf.) Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, half the
@Dijon Mustard{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), remaining
Fry Seasoning, @salt{¾%tsp}, and @pepper{some}. Mix to thoroughly combine, then
form into two 1-inch-tall loaves.

> Wet your hands or coat with oil first to prevent sticking.

Coat a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @oil{some}. Add meatloaves to
prepared sheet. Tent meatloaves with #foil{}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Cranberry Dijon Glaze ==

While meatloaves roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Cranberry Jam{2%tablespoon},
half the @Ketchup{1%tablespoon}, and remaining mustard.

When meatloaves are done, remove sheet from oven; remove foil. Top loaves with
cranberry glaze.

Return to oven until glaze is tacky, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== Toasted Almond Jumble ==

Meanwhile, heat a #small dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@Almonds{½%ounce} and cook, stirring often, until golden brown and toasted,
~{2-4%minutes}.

When veggies are done, add toasted almonds and @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce} to
sheet with veggies. Season with @salt{some} and @pepper{some}; toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Divide meatloaves and roasted veggies between plates. Serve.